					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The sound does not kill the worms. The sound only resonates them apart after they go dormant from a lack of food (total conversion of the garment). When they are still alive and active, they can &quot;hang on&quot; to each other and not fall apart. Once they go dormant, however, they unravel because they aren't reacting.</p> 
