					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Downvoted due to problems of scale. In all likelihood to be as small in diameter as a cotton fiber (you know&#8230;so it will be mistaken for one) this organism would have to be a single-celled organism. We're talking about three orders of magnitude from millimeters (worms diameters) to micrometers (the diameter of fibers like cotton).</p> 
				 	]]>
